    ],
    "sizes": [
      10.079999923706055
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      54.25,
      72.18,
      544.94,
      86.61
    ],
    "text": "Thereafter, seventeen issues were recorded on behalf of the Plaintiff and four issues had",
    "fonts": [
      "CenturySchoolbook"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      54.25,
      93.78,
      288.69,
      108.21
    ],
    "text": "been recorded on behalf of the Defendant.",
    "fonts": [
      "CenturySchoolbook"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      54.25,
      136.98,
      544.94,
      151.4
    ],
    "text": "Only one witness gave evidence on behalf of the Bank and it is worthy of note that the",
    "fonts": [
      "CenturySchoolbook"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      54.25,
      158.82,
      529.6,
      173.24
    ],
    "text": "testimony of this witness has not been contradicted by way of any contrary evidence.",
    "fonts": [
      "CenturySchoolbook"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      54.25,
      202.02,
      545.05,
      216.44
    ],
    "text": "In this connection, this Court wishes to cite the case of Cinemas Limited v.",
    "fonts": [
      "CenturySchoolbook",
      "CenturySchoolbook-BoldIt"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      54.25,
      223.62,
      545.05,
      238.04
    ],
    "text": "Sounderarajan2 which endorsed the decision of former Chief Justice H. N. G. Fernando",
    "fonts": [
      "CenturySchoolbook",
      "CenturySchoolbook-BoldIt"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      7.919999599456787,
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      54.25,
      245.22,
      544.94,
      259.65
    ],
    "text": "in the case of Edrick De Silva Vs. Chandradasa De Silva.3 These cases are to the",
    "fonts": [
      "CenturySchoolbook",
      "CenturySchoolbook-BoldIt"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      7.919999599456787,
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      54.25,
      266.82,
      544.94,
      281.25
    ],
    "text": "effect that when one party leads evidence and the other party does not lead any contrary",
    "fonts": [
      "CenturySchoolbook",
      "CenturySchoolbook-BoldIt"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      54.25,
      288.66,
      544.94,
      303.08
    ],
    "text": "evidence, the evidence that has been led on behalf of the Plaintiff has to be accepted as",
    "fonts": [
      "CenturySchoolbook"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      54.25,
      310.26,
      84.25,
      324.68
    ],
    "text": "true.",
    "fonts": [
      "CenturySchoolbook"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      54.25,
      353.46,
      544.93,
      367.89
    ],
    "text": "In the circumstances, in the absence of any contrary evidence led on behalf of the",
    "fonts": [
      "CenturySchoolbook"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      54.25,
      375.06,
      544.94,
      389.49
    ],
    "text": "Defendant, it is quite clear that the Plaintiff has established its case against the",
    "fonts": [
      "CenturySchoolbook"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      54.25,
      396.66,
      544.93,
      411.08
    ],
    "text": "Defendant based on the documents and the oral evidence. However, the only point of",
    "fonts": [
      "CenturySchoolbook"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      54.25,
      418.5,
      544.95,
      432.93
    ],
    "text": "contention that seems to arise between the parties is the question of interest that has to",
    "fonts": [
      "CenturySchoolbook"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      54.25,
      440.1,
      122.72,
      454.52
    ],
    "text": "be imposed.",
    "fonts": [
      "CenturySchoolbook"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      54.25,
      483.3,
      544.94,
      497.73
    ],
    "text": "It is true that the loan application, mortgage bond and the statement of accounts all",
    "fonts": [
      "CenturySchoolbook"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      54.25,
      504.9,
      544.93,
      519.33
    ],
    "text": "referred to different rates of interest. However, the learned High Court Judge has chosen",
    "fonts": [
      "CenturySchoolbook"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      54.25,
      526.5,
      544.94,
      540.92
    ],
    "text": "to accept the interest rate that has been imposed in the statement of accounts, namely,",
    "fonts": [
      "CenturySchoolbook"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      54.25,
      548.34,
      161.62,
      562.76
    ],
    "text": "the rate of 17.15%.",
    "fonts": [
      "CenturySchoolbook"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      54.25,
      591.54,
      544.94,
      605.96
    ],
    "text": "It is worthy of note that even though the Defendant was not sued on the mortgage bonds,",
    "fonts": [
      "CenturySchoolbook"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      54.25,
      613.14,
      544.93,
      627.57
    ],
    "text": "the Defendant had agreed with the Plaintiff Bank to a variable rate of interest. In terms",
    "fonts": [
      "CenturySchoolbook"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      54.25,
      634.74,
      544.93,
      649.16
    ],
    "text": "of clause (f) of the mortgage bond, it is specifically stated that the interest on the",
    "fonts": [
      "CenturySchoolbook"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      54.25,
      656.34,
      544.93,
      670.76
    ],
    "text": "aforesaid outstanding sums of money could be fixed at \u201csuch other or higher rate or rates",
    "fonts": [
      "CenturySchoolbook",
      "CenturySchoolbook-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      54.25,
      678.18,
      544.94,
      692.6
    ],
    "text": "as may from time to time be fixed or charged by the Bank or by the direction of or by the",
    "fonts": [
      "CenturySchoolbook-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      54.25,
      699.78,
      544.92,
      714.2
    ],
    "text": "General Manager for the time being of the Bank according to the sole and absolute",
    "fonts": [
      "CenturySchoolbook-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      54.25,
      728.94,
      200.75,
      769.04
    ],
    "text": "2 [1998] 2 Sri LR 16 3 70 NLR 169 at p 174.",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri",
      "CenturySchoolbook"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      6.960000038146973,
      10.079999923706055,
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      359.11,
      774.87,
      535.16,
      786.99
    ],
    "text": "SC / CHC / APPEAL / 47 / 2019 5",
    "fonts": [
      "CenturySchoolbook-Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      10.079999923706055
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      54.25,
      72.18,
      544.92,
      86.61
    ],
    "text": "discretion of the said General Manager and according to the usual course of business to",
    "fonts": [
      "CenturySchoolbook-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      54.25,
      93.78,
      544.92,
      108.21
    ],
    "text": "be computed from the date or respective dates of such loans advances or payments being",
    "fonts": [
      "CenturySchoolbook-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      54.25,
      115.38,
      453.91,
      129.81
    ],
    "text": "made or of the overdrafts being allowed or of the promissory notes\u2026\u2026..\u201d",
    "fonts": [
      "CenturySchoolbook",
      "CenturySchoolbook-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      54.25,
      158.82,
      544.94,
      173.24
    ],
    "text": "This clause makes it quite clear that the Bank could impose the variable rate of interest",
    "fonts": [
      "CenturySchoolbook"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      54.25,
      180.42,
      544.94,
      194.85
    ],
    "text": "found in the statement of accounts. The Plaintiff and the Defendant have agreed to this",
    "fonts": [
      "CenturySchoolbook"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      54.25,
      202.02,
      544.93,
      216.44
    ],
    "text": "course of action being adopted and therefore, since no issues have been raised on the",
    "fonts": [
      "CenturySchoolbook"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      54.25,
      223.62,
      544.93,
      238.04
    ],
    "text": "unconscionability of this clause, this Court takes the view that this cannot form a",
    "fonts": [
      "CenturySchoolbook"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      54.25,
      245.22,
      281.81,
      259.65
    ],
    "text": "question of law either before this Court.",
    "fonts": [
      "CenturySchoolbook"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      54.25,
      288.66,
      544.94,
      303.08
    ],
    "text": "The learned Commercial High Court judge himself has considered this aspect of the",
    "fonts": [
      "CenturySchoolbook"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      54.25,
      310.26,
      544.94,
      324.68
    ],
    "text": "matter at page 06 of his judgment dated 26 of April 2019 and concluded that the",
    "fonts": [
      "CenturySchoolbook"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      54.25,
      331.86,
      275.61,
      346.29
    ],
    "text": "imposition of this interest is not illegal.",
    "fonts": [
      "CenturySchoolbook"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      54.25,
      375.3,
      544.94,
      389.73
    ],
    "text": "In the case of Paragon Finance v. Nash4, it has been established that Banks and",
    "fonts": [
      "CenturySchoolbook",
      "CenturySchoolbook-Bold",
      "CenturySchoolbook-BoldIt",
      "Roboto-Regular"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      7.919999599456787,
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      54.25,
      397.14,
      544.94,
      411.57
    ],
    "text": "financial institutions do enjoy the discretion to impose variable rates of interest on their",
    "fonts": [
      "CenturySchoolbook"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      54.25,
      418.74,
      435.4,
      433.17
    ],
    "text": "loan agreements but the discretion has to be exercised reasonably.",
    "fonts": [
      "CenturySchoolbook"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      54.25,
      461.94,
      544.94,
      476.36
    ],
    "text": "In the circumstances, we find that the case of the Plaintiff has been proved and that the",
    "fonts": [
      "CenturySchoolbook"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      54.25,
      483.54,
      544.93,
      497.96
    ],
    "text": "High Court Judge has arrived at a correct finding and we see no reasons to interfere with",
    "fonts": [
      "CenturySchoolbook"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      54.25,
      505.38,
      544.94,
      519.8
    ],
    "text": "the judgment rendered by the Commercial High Court. We affirm the judgment and we",
    "fonts": [
      "CenturySchoolbook"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      54.25,
      526.98,
      443.83,
      541.4
    ],
    "text": "proceed to dismiss the appeal preferred by the Defendant - Appellant.",
    "fonts": [
      "CenturySchoolbook"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      54.25,
      570.18,
      544.93,
      584.6
    ],
    "text": "We place on record our appreciation of the arguments placed before this Court by the",
    "fonts": [
      "CenturySchoolbook"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      54.25,
      591.78,
      544.94,
      606.21
    ],
    "text": "young Attorney-at-Law, Mr. Rajinda Kandegedara who represented the Defendant \u2013",
    "fonts": [
      "CenturySchoolbook"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      54.25,
      613.38,
      122.27,
      627.8
    ],
    "text": "Appellant.",
    "fonts": [
      "CenturySchoolbook"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
